Mr. Peter Obi, presidential candidate of the Labour Party says has achieved success in life by the grace of God, and is only running for president because he loves humanity. The former Anambra State said he’s a contented person and won’t consider serving in another person’s government. Obi who spoke on Saturday in his hometown of Agulu in Anambra State, noted that his desire to serve the people prompted him to run for president. Watch video below. Credit: Arise TV.